### 2. Algorithm Architecture

The tool is built on a three-layer architecture: [claude](https://claude.ai/public/artifacts/2ed69e79-7c50-489f-849e-e18116356ae9)

#### A. Core Model
- **Algorithm:** XGBoost (eXtreme Gradient Boosting)
- **Claim:** Winner of most Kaggle forecasting competitions
- **Performance:** Consistently outperforms ARIMA, Prophet, and LSTM models
- **Library Version:** XGBoost v2.1 [claude](https://claude.ai/public/artifacts/2ed69e79-7c50-489f-849e-e18116356ae9)

#### B. Feature Engine
The feature engineering layer includes:
- **Lag features** — historical values at different time lags
- **Rolling statistics** — computed over 7-day, 14-day, and 30-day windows
- **Seasonal decomposition** — extracting seasonal patterns
- **Trend extraction** — identifying long-term directional movement
- **Fourier terms** — for modeling cyclicality/periodic patterns [claude](https://claude.ai/public/artifacts/2ed69e79-7c50-489f-849e-e18116356ae9)

#### C. Ensemble Layer
A weighted blend of three models:
- **XGBoost:** 60% weight
- **Holt-Winters (Exponential Smoothing):** 20% weight
- **Linear Trend:** 20% weight
- **Purpose:** Reduces variance and boosts stability [claude](https://claude.ai/public/artifacts/2ed69e79-7c50-489f-849e-e18116356ae9)

#### D. Accuracy Metrics
- **MAPE (Mean Absolute Percentage Error):** Consistently below 3% on retail/supply chain data
- **SMAPE (Symmetric Mean Absolute Percentage Error):** Used as the loss function for symmetric error optimization
- **Historical MAPE benchmark:** 2.1% [claude](https://claude.ai/public/artifacts/2ed69e79-7c50-489f-849e-e18116356ae9)

